  <name>USB Enforcer</name>
  <summary>USB data loss prevention for Linux desktops</summary>
  
  <description>
    <p>
      USB Enforcer is a data loss prevention (DLP) system for Linux desktops that enforces
      encryption on USB mass-storage devices. Plaintext USB devices are automatically forced
      read-only, while LUKS2-encrypted devices can be unlocked and mounted with write access.
    </p>
    <p>Key Features:</p>
    <ul>
      <li>Automatic detection and classification of USB storage devices</li>
      <li>Block-level enforcement of read-only mode for plaintext devices</li>
      <li>Support for LUKS2-encrypted USB drives</li>
      <li>Desktop notifications for USB events</li>
      <li>GTK4 wizard for encrypting drives</li>
      <li>Configurable group-based exemptions</li>
      <li>Integration with systemd, udev, DBus, and PolicyKit</li>
    </ul>
    <p>
      The system consists of a daemon that watches for USB devices via udev, enforces
      encryption policies, and provides a DBus API. A user-session UI bridge displays
      desktop notifications and can launch the encryption wizard when needed.
    </p>
  </description>
  
